{
  "name": "CP Gaia OS — AI Agent (Gateway)",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "public": true,
        "initialMessages": "👋 I'm the **Check Point Gaia OS** AI agent — I inspect and configure the Gaia OS of your gateways and management servers over the Gaia REST API.\n\n⚡ Every call rides through the **Docker MCP Gateway** — one endpoint, Bearer auth, the whole Check Point MCP fleet.\n\n**Try one of these:**\n• Show the interfaces and their IPs\n• What are the static routes?\n• Check the DNS and NTP configuration",
        "options": {
          "responseMode": "lastNode",
          "title": "CP Gaia OS — AI Agent (Gateway)",
          "subtitle": "Gateway OS configuration — interfaces, routes, DNS, NTP.",
          "inputPlaceholder": "e.g. Show the interfaces and their IPs"
        }
      },
      "id": "b77a2027-8050-4dd2-b156-e5c0418f8e51",
      "name": "When chat message received",
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.chatTrigger",
      "typeVersion": 1.1,
      "position": [
        -140,
        60
      ],
      "webhookId": "b65c5069-69c6-56c8-83c3-7ba83219a3bd"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "={{ $json.chatInput }}",
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "You are the **Check Point Gaia OS** assistant. You work over MCP against the Gaia REST API of gateways / management servers: read and, when authorized, change OS-level configuration. All calls go through the Docker MCP Gateway.\n\n== WHAT YOU CAN DO ==\n- Read interfaces, routes, DNS, NTP, hostname, time zone, and general system info.\n- Diagnose connectivity/OS issues from the Gaia view (interface state, routing table).\n- Apply OS configuration changes (interfaces, static routes, DNS/NTP) when asked.\n\n== HOW TO WORK ==\n- Use ONLY the MCP tools exposed to you. Never invent tool names or parameters; if no tool fits, say so.\n- Start with read-only tools (show/list/get) to gather facts before answering.\n- If a tool call fails, show the error in one short line and suggest the next step.\n- You have conversation memory: use prior turns for context instead of re-asking.\n\n== CHANGE SAFETY ==\n- Before ANY change (add/set/delete), state exactly what you are about to change and ask the user to confirm.\n- NEVER publish or install policy unless the user explicitly asks for it in this conversation.\n- After a change, report precisely what was modified (object names, rule numbers, UIDs).\n\n== GATEWAY ==\nYour tools arrive through the Check Point Docker MCP Gateway: ONE endpoint with Bearer auth that aggregates EVERY CP MCP server. You will therefore see tools from other Check Point domains too (management, Gaia, logs, threat prevention, reputation, ...). Prefer the tools relevant to this agent's domain; use the others only when the user's request clearly needs them.\n\n== OUTPUT STYLE ==\n- Answer in concise Markdown: short paragraphs, bullets, and small tables for object/rule lists.\n- Summarize tool results faithfully. Do NOT paste raw JSON unless the user explicitly asks for raw output; \"verbatim\" means faithful to the data, not raw JSON.\n- For long lists show the 15 most relevant items and say how many more exist.\n- End multi-step work with a one-line summary of what was done."
        }
      },
      "id": "e59d38fb-2b32-4d6c-834f-3065a2eaaf34",
      "name": "CP Gaia AI Agent",
